notesStmt.note: Title for manuscript from caption title for predominant work (f. 6r).

msContents.summary: Treatise on astrology, concluding with a table of contents, followed by a short work on arithmetic applied to astrology and a detailed horoscope written as for an unnamed distant relative of the grand duke, aged 21 in 1609.

supportDesc.extent: 174 leaves : 217 x 157 (174 x 108) mm. bound to 222 x 165 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 174; [ii], 1-149, [150-172]; contemporary foliation in ink, modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto. Catchwords, lower right verso.

binding.p: Contemporary armorial vellum (Zacour-Hirsch) with remnants of pink and green fabric ties inside lower cover.

origin.p: Written in Italy in the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Marzucchi sale, Florence, 1827 (Zacour-Hirsch); formerly in the library of Prince Baldassare Boncompagni of Rome (no. 544, label on cover).
